Edward A. Diebolt House is a historic home located at Buffalo in Erie County, New York.  It is a Colonial Revival style frame house built in 1922â€“1923. It is representative of the standardized floor plan home constructed in the immediate post-World War I period and retains complete integrity.
It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2006.  It is located in the University Park Historic District.
